org.akubraproject.rmi
Class AkubraRMIClient

java.lang.Object
  org.akubraproject.rmi.AkubraRMIClient

public class AkubraRMIClient
extends Object

A Utility class that helps applications to locate an Akubra RMI Server and create a BlobStore that forwards all operations to that server.

Author:
Pradeep Krishnan

create

public static org.akubraproject.BlobStore create()
                                          throws IOException,
                                                 NotBoundException
Creates a client to a default akubra-rmi-server running on localhost. The default RMI registry running on localhost is used for the lookup.

Returns:
an RMI client BlobStore with a generated id
Throws:
IOException - on an error in contacting the server
NotBoundException - when a server with AkubraRMIServer.DEFAULT_SERVER_NAME is not bound

create

public static org.akubraproject.BlobStore create(URI serverUri)
                                          throws IOException,
                                                 NotBoundException
Creates a client to the given akubra-rmi-server.

Parameters:
serverUri - a URI of the form rmi://registryHost:registryPort/serverName. The registryPort can be omitted in which case it defaults to the default RMI registry port. The 'serverName' is the registered name of the akubra-rmi-server at the RMI registry.
Returns:
an RMI client BlobStore with a generated id
Throws:
IOException - on an error in contacting the server
NotBoundException - when a server with the given serverName is not bound

locateServer

public static RemoteStore locateServer(URI uri)
                                throws RemoteException,
                                       NotBoundException
Locates an akubra-rmi-server using the given uri.

Parameters:
uri - a URI of the form rmi://registryHost:registryPort/serverName. The registryPort can be omitted in which case it defaults to the default RMI registry port. The 'serverName' is the registered name of the akubra-rmi-server at the RMI registry.
Returns:
a client side stub to talk to the remote akubra-rmi-server
Throws:
RemoteException - on contacting the RMI registry
NotBoundException - when a server with the given serverName is not bound
